<h2>How it works</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Minimum characters:</strong> Users must type at least 3 characters before search begins</li>
    <li><strong>Debouncing:</strong> Search requests are debounced (250ms delay) to avoid excessive API calls</li>
    <li><strong>Real-time results:</strong> Results appear in a dropdown below the input as the user types</li>
    <li><strong>Selection:</strong> Users can click on a result to select it, or use keyboard navigation (arrow keys, Enter)</li>
    <li><strong>Hidden fields:</strong> Selected user data is stored in hidden inputs (object ID, name, email)</li>
    <li><strong>Visual feedback:</strong> Spinner shows while searching, message provides guidance</li>
</li>

<h2>Required JavaScript</h2>
<p>
    The user-picker component requires the <code>user-picker.js</code> script to be loaded. This script handles:
</p>
<ul>
    <li>Debounced search requests to <code>/api/users/search</code></li>
    <li>Displaying search results in a dropdown</li>
    <li>Handling user selection</li>
    <li>Updating hidden form fields</li>
    <li>Keyboard navigation support</li>
</ul>

<pre><code>&lt;script src="~/js/user-picker.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;</code></pre>

<h2>Usage guidelines</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Use this pattern when adding or changing contacts, team members, or assigned users</li>
    <li>Always include helpful placeholder text (e.g., "e.g. Alex Smith or alex.smith@education.gov.uk")</li>
    <li>Provide clear instructions about the minimum character requirement</li>
    <li>Show selected user information clearly after selection</li>
    <li>Handle "no results" state gracefully</li>
    <li>Support keyboard navigation for accessibility</li>
</ul>

<h2>Accessibility</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Provide clear labels for search inputs</li>
    <li>Ensure keyboard navigation works (arrow keys, Enter to select, Escape to close)</li>
    <li>Use <code>role="listbox"</code> and <code>aria-live="polite"</code> for results</li>
    <li>Announce search results to screen readers</li>
    <li>Provide clear feedback when no results are found</li>
    <li>Ensure the spinner is marked with <code>aria-hidden="true"</code></li>
</ul>

@section Scripts {
    <script src="~/js/user-picker.js"></script>
}
